"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:13:03.001Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alisha/.claude/plans/glowing-imagining-dove.md\",\"oldString\":\"# E2E Triage: Remove Auto-trigger, Show Report Instead of Issues, Add Triage Link to Slack\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe e2e-triage workflow currently auto-runs on every E2E failure and creates GitHub issues for real bugs. The desired behavior is:\\n1. **No GitHub issues** for real bugs — just show a report in CI logs\\n2. **Flaky tests** — still try to fix and open PRs (keep existing behavior)\\n3. **No auto-trigger** — remove `workflow_run` trigger; keep `workflow_dispatch` only\\n4. **Slack invocation** — add a \\\"Triage\\\" link in the E2E failure Slack message so someone can manually trigger triage\\n5. **60-min timeout** — already in place, no change needed\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. `e2e-triage.yml` — Remove auto-trigger\\n\\n- **Remove** the `workflow_run` trigger (lines 3-6)\\n- **Keep** `workflow_dispatch` with `run_id` input\\n- Everything else stays the same (60-min timeout, artifact download, Claude triage run)\\n\\n### 2. `SKILL.md` — CI mode: report instead of GitHub issues for real bugs\\n\\nIn **Step 4b** (CI Mode actions):\\n\\n- **For `real-bug` failures**: Replace issue creation with a **CI report** — print a structured report to stdout (visible in CI logs / GitHub Actions step output). No `gh issue create` or `gh issue comment`.\\n- **For `flaky` failures**: Keep existing PR creation behavior unchanged.\\n- **Update the Claude prompt** in `e2e-triage.yml` to say \\\"For real bugs: print a detailed report (do NOT create GitHub issues)\\\" instead of the current \\\"For real bugs: create or comment on GitHub issues\\\"\\n- **Update `triage-summary.json`** schema: real-bug entries use `action_type: \\\"report\\\"` instead of `\\\"issue\\\"` / `\\\"comment\\\"`\\n- **Remove** `gh issue list`, `gh issue create`, `gh issue comment` from `allowedTools` in triage workflow\\n\\n### 3. `e2e.yml` — Add triage link to Slack failure message\\n\\nIn the `notify-slack` job, add a line to the Slack message with a link to manually trigger triage:\\n\\n```\\n<https://github.com/{repo}/actions/workflows/e2e-triage.yml|:mag: Triage these failures> (use run ID: `{run_id}`)\\n```\\n\\nThis gives the user a direct link to the workflow_dispatch page and the run ID to paste in.\\n\\n### 4. `README.md` — Update description\\n\\nUpdate the README to reflect the new behavior (no auto-trigger, no issues, report-only for real bugs).\\n\\n### 5. `e2e-triage.yml` — Remove issue-related permissions\\n\\nRemove `issues: write` from the permissions block since we no longer create issues.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n1. `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml` — remove `workflow_run` trigger, remove issue permissions, update Claude prompt\\n2. `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` — add triage link to Slack failure message\\n3. `.claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md` — replace issue creation with CI report for real bugs\\n4. `.claude/skills/e2e-triage/README.md` — update description\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. Review the updated `e2e-triage.yml` to confirm no `workflow_run` trigger remains\\n2. Check that `SKILL.md` CI mode no longer references `gh issue create/comment`\\n3. Verify the Slack message in `e2e.yml` includes the triage link with run ID\\n4. The `allowedTools` in the triage prompt no longer includes `gh issue *` commands\",\"newString\":\"# Fix: E2E Triage PR creation blocked by GITHUB_TOKEN permissions\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe e2e-triage workflow's Claude agent creates PRs for flaky test fixes via `gh pr create`. This fails because `GH_TOKEN` is set to `${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}` — the default Actions token which can't push branches or create PRs when branch protection is enabled.\\n\\nThe `release.yml` workflow already solves this pattern using `actions/create-github-app-token@v2.2.1` to generate a GitHub App token with elevated permissions.\\n\\n## Problem\\n\\nIn `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml` line 73:\\n```yaml\\nGH_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\\n```\\n\\nThe Claude agent uses `GH_TOKEN` for `git push` and `gh pr create`, both of which need a token with repo push + PR write access that `GITHUB_TOKEN` doesn't provide under branch protection.\\n\\n## Fix\\n\\n### `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml`\\n\\nAdd a GitHub App token generation step (same pattern as `release.yml`), then use it for `GH_TOKEN` in the triage step.\\n\\n1. **Add a new step** before \\\"Run triage\\\" to generate an app token:\\n   ```yaml\\n   - name: Generate GitHub App token\\n     id: app-token\\n     uses: actions/create-github-app-token@v2.2.1\\n     with:\\n       app-id: ${{ secrets.TRIAGE_APP_ID }}\\n       private-key: ${{ secrets.TRIAGE_APP_PRIVATE_KEY }}\\n   ```\\n\\n2. **Update `GH_TOKEN`** in the \\\"Run triage\\\" step (line 73):\\n   ```yaml\\n   GH_TOKEN: ${{ steps.app-token.outputs.token }}\\n   ```\\n\\n3. **Also update `GH_TOKEN`** in the \\\"Download E2E artifacts\\\" step (line 43) to use the same app token for consistency (artifact downloads also need actions read access).\\n\\n**Note:** This requires the repo to have a GitHub App configured with `contents: write` and `pull_requests: write` permissions, and its credentials stored as `TRIAGE_APP_ID` / `TRIAGE_APP_PRIVATE_KEY` secrets. If a shared app already exists (check with user), reuse those secret names instead.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n- The workflow YAML is syntactically valid\\n- The app-token step precedes steps that use `GH_TOKEN`\\n- `GH_TOKEN` in both \\\"Download E2E artifacts\\\" and \\\"Run triage\\\" uses `${{ steps.app-token.outputs.token }}`\",\"originalFile\":\"# E2E Triage: Remove Auto-trigger, Show Report Instead of Issues, Add Triage Link to Slack\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe e2e-triage workflow currently auto-runs on every E2E failure and creates GitHub issues for real bugs. The desired behavior is:\\n1. **No GitHub issues** for real bugs — just show a report in CI logs\\n2. **Flaky tests** — still try to fix and open PRs (keep existing behavior)\\n3. **No auto-trigger** — remove `workflow_run` trigger; keep `workflow_dispatch` only\\n4. **Slack invocation** — add a \\\"Triage\\\" link in the E2E failure Slack message so someone can manually trigger triage\\n5. **60-min timeout** — already in place, no change needed\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. `e2e-triage.yml` — Remove auto-trigger\\n\\n- **Remove** the `workflow_run` trigger (lines 3-6)\\n- **Keep** `workflow_dispatch` with `run_id` input\\n- Everything else stays the same (60-min timeout, artifact download, Claude triage run)\\n\\n### 2. `SKILL.md` — CI mode: report instead of GitHub issues for real bugs\\n\\nIn **Step 4b** (CI Mode actions):\\n\\n- **For `real-bug` failures**: Replace issue creation with a **CI report** — print a structured report to stdout (visible in CI logs / GitHub Actions step output). No `gh issue create` or `gh issue comment`.\\n- **For `flaky` failures**: Keep existing PR creation behavior unchanged.\\n- **Update the Claude prompt** in `e2e-triage.yml` to say \\\"For real bugs: print a detailed report (do NOT create GitHub issues)\\\" instead of the current \\\"For real bugs: create or comment on GitHub issues\\\"\\n- **Update `triage-summary.json`** schema: real-bug entries use `action_type: \\\"report\\\"` instead of `\\\"issue\\\"` / `\\\"comment\\\"`\\n- **Remove** `gh issue list`, `gh issue create`, `gh issue comment` from `allowedTools` in triage workflow\\n\\n### 3. `e2e.yml` — Add triage link to Slack failure message\\n\\nIn the `notify-slack` job, add a line to the Slack message with a link to manually trigger triage:\\n\\n```\\n<https://github.com/{repo}/actions/workflows/e2e-triage.yml|:mag: Triage these failures> (use run ID: `{run_id}`)\\n```\\n\\nThis gives the user a direct link to the workflow_dispatch page and the run ID to paste in.\\n\\n### 4. `README.md` — Update description\\n\\nUpdate the README to reflect the new behavior (no auto-trigger, no issues, report-only for real bugs).\\n\\n### 5. `e2e-triage.yml` — Remove issue-related permissions\\n\\nRemove `issues: write` from the permissions block since we no longer create issues.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n1. `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml` — remove `workflow_run` trigger, remove issue permissions, update Claude prompt\\n2. `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` — add triage link to Slack failure message\\n3. `.claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md` — replace issue creation with CI report for real bugs\\n4. `.claude/skills/e2e-triage/README.md` — update description\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. Review the updated `e2e-triage.yml` to confirm no `workflow_run` trigger remains\\n2. Check that `SKILL.md` CI mode no longer references `gh issue create/comment`\\n3. Verify the Slack message in `e2e.yml` includes the triage link with run ID\\n4. The `allowedTools` in the triage prompt no longer includes `gh issue *` commands\\n\",\"structuredPatch\":[{\"oldStart\":1,\"oldLines\":60,\"newStart\":1,\"newLines\":47,\"lines\":[\"-# E2E Triage: Remove Auto-trigger, Show Report Instead of Issues, Add Triage Link to Slack\",\"+# Fix: E2E Triage PR creation blocked by GITHUB_TOKEN permissions\",\" \",\" ## Context\",\" \",\"-The e2e-triage workflow currently auto-runs on every E2E failure and creates GitHub issues for real bugs. The desired behavior is:\",\"-1. **No GitHub issues** for real bugs — just show a report in CI logs\",\"-2. **Flaky tests** — still try to fix and open PRs (keep existing behavior)\",\"-3. **No auto-trigger** — remove `workflow_run` trigger; keep `workflow_dispatch` only\",\"-4. **Slack invocation** — add a \\\"Triage\\\" link in the E2E failure Slack message so someone can manually trigger triage\",\"-5. **60-min timeout** — already in place, no change needed\",\"+The e2e-triage workflow's Claude agent creates PRs for flaky test fixes via `gh pr create`. This fails because `GH_TOKEN` is set to `${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}` — the default Actions token which can't p